'''Janet Linn''' is a nurse at [[Pacific Northwest General Hospital]].

==History==
===Helipad Elevator===
Janet found Alex and informed him that an inspector said the helipad elevator wasn't up to code. ''("[[Back in the Saddle]]")''

===Halloween===
On Halloween, Janet was gossiping with other nurses about the hospital being haunted because of all the ICU patients coding and the skeletons buried outside. Alex interrupted them, corrected their information, and told them to get back to work. ''("[[Whistlin' Past the Graveyard]]")''

===Hospital Purchase===
Janet showed up to work one day and learned the hospital had been purchased by the [[Catherine Fox Foundation]] and she'd have to report to [[Grey Sloan Memorial Hospital]] to interview to keep her job. She cried with another nurse. ''("[[Save the Last Dance for Me]]")''

==Career==
She is a nurse at [[Pacific Northwest General Hospital]].

==Notes and Trivia==
*Janet was credited as Pac-North Nurse in her first appearance.
